This paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT) and microeconomics (cs.EC). The focus is on designing efficient mechanisms for bilateral trading, which involves allocation and pricing of a single item, making it relevant to topics in optimization (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of statistical data, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG).
